<section xml:id="_dir_0cd17818026a7be52077794beeee002c_1autotoc_md190">
<title>Introduction</title>
<para><emphasis><emphasis role="bold"><link linkend="_namespace_luthetus_1_1_text_editor">Luthetus.TextEditor</link></emphasis></emphasis> is a Text Editor component library using the <link xlink:href="https://dotnet.microsoft.com/en-us/apps/aspnet/web-apps/blazor">Blazor UI Framework</link> for <link xlink:href="https://dotnet.microsoft.com/">.NET</link></para>
</section>
<section xml:id="_dir_0cd17818026a7be52077794beeee002c_1autotoc_md191">
<title>Goal</title>
<para>The aim of <link linkend="_namespace_luthetus_1_1_text_editor">Luthetus.TextEditor</link> is to replicate the features of the <link xlink:href="https://microsoft.github.io/monaco-editor/">Monaco Editor</link> that powers <link xlink:href="https://code.visualstudio.com/">Visual Studio Code</link> using Blazor.</para>

<para>One can make use of this Text Editor by referencing the Nuget Package or cloning the source code and referencing it directly.</para>
</section>
